Surviving the winter is almost the only wish of the animals living on the Tibetan plateau. But some animals have higher aspirations, and for them, reproduction is as important as survival. The Tibetan plateau in winter seems to be a huge breeding ground, and this love season has been going on for thousands of years. About 'Journeys in Nature': Snowy Qinghai Lake Series Qinghai Lake, the largest saltwater, inland lake in China, is home to a large number of wild animals. CGTN Nature's film crew traveled to Qinghai and discovered rare animal and plant species. During the Spring Festival, we will present the beautiful nature of China â€“ "Journeys in Nature": Snowy Qinghai Lake Series, showing the wonderful creatures in winter. For more: Snowy Qinghai Lake Series | Episode 1: Snowy Lake Snowy Qinghai Lake Series | Episode 2: Swan lake on ice Snowy Qinghai Lake Series | Episode 3: Journey to the south Snowy Qinghai Lake Series | Episode 4: Battles for love Snowy Qinghai Lake Series | Episode 5: Broken dreams (Cover image is a screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.) 